Project: Book My Ticket â€“ Online Movie Ticket Booking System

Description:
Developed a full-stack web application for online movie ticket booking with separate Admin and User modules. 
The system allows users to browse movies, select shows and seats, make online payments, and receive QR-coded tickets, 
while admins manage movies, theaters, screens, seat layouts, and users.

Technologies Used:
Java, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, Thymeleaf, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, MySQL, Spring Security

Key Features:
Role-based authentication for Admin and User
OTP-based email verification using JavaMailSender
Movie and theater image upload using Cloudinary
Online ticket booking with Razorpay payment gateway
Real-time seat selection and booking
QR code generation for ticket confirmation
Admin user management (block/unblock users)

Integrations:
Razorpay, Cloudinary, JavaMailSender, QR Code Generator

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Short Explanation:
Book My Ticket is an online movie ticket booking application developed using Spring Boot and Thymeleaf. 
It has two modules: Admin and User.
Admins can manage movies, theaters, screens, seat layouts, and users, while users can register using OTP-based email verification,
view available shows, book seats, make payments using Razorpay, and receive QR-coded tickets. Cloudinary is used for image storage,
and MySQL is used for database management.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Detailed Explanation:
This project is a full-stack Spring Boot application with Thymeleaf as the frontend.
It has two roles: Admin and User.
The Admin module allows admins to log in securely and manage movies, theaters, screens, seat layouts, and show timings. 
Admins can also view registered users and block or unblock them.
The User module allows users to register and verify their email using OTP sent via JavaMailSender. 
After login, users can browse movies, select shows, choose seats, and proceed with booking.

For payments, Razorpay is integrated to handle secure online transactions. Once payment is successful, 
a booking is created and a QR code is generated for the ticket, which can be used for entry validation.

Images of movies and theaters are stored in Cloudinary to reduce server load. MySQL is used for storing user,
 booking, show, and payment data using JPA and Hibernate.

Architecture Explanation:

Controller Layer â†’ Handles requests
Service Layer â†’ Business logic
Repository Layer â†’ Database operations using JPA
Frontend â†’ Thymeleaf templates
Database â†’ MySQL, Redis 

